article.headline: East Carolina 89, Coastal Carolina 64
article.story: GREENVILLE, N.C. (AP) -- Sam Hinnant scored 23 points and led four players in double figures as East Carolina defeated Coastal Carolina 89-64 on Wednesday night. James Legan had 19 points for the Pirates (5-7), while John Fields scored 11 and Brandon Evans, 10. Jack Leasure led Coastal Carolina (6-6) with 16 points, and Everage Richardson had 13. Mario Sisinni added 10. East Carolina was perfect at the free throw line in the first half, shooting 7-of-7 and made 9-of-11 in the second half. Both teams shot poorly in the second half, with the Chanticleers getting just 34.5 percent of their shots and ECU connecting on 36.1 percent.
